<style>
  .article_column-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 320px;
    border-radius: 11px;
  }
  img.article_column-image {
    overflow: hidden;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 50% 50%;
  }
  .article_column-image-border {
    border: 1px solid rgba(60, 31, 27, 0.30);
  }
  .article_column {
      height: max-content;
  }
  .article_column-third {
    width: calc(33.3333334% - 33.3333334px);
  }
  .article_column-half {
    width: calc(50% - 25px);
  }
  .article_column-text-third-top {
    padding-top: 81px;
  }
  .article_column-text ul {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
    color: #3c1f1b;
    margin-top: -10px;
    padding-left: 34px;
  }
  @media(max-width: 1450px) {
    .article_column-half {
    width: calc(50% - 15px);
  }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
      gap: 30px;
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 114px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 1250px) {
    .article_column-third {
        width: calc(50% - 15px);
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 81px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 950px) {
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 114px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 750px) {
    .article_column-text ul {
      margin-top: -12px;
      padding-left: 32px;
    }
    .article_column-text-third-top {
      padding-top: 0;
    }
    .article_column-half {
      width: 100%
    }
    .article_column-third {
        width: 100%;
        gap: 30px;
    }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
        gap: 30px;
    }
    .rebranding_container {
        gap: 40px;
    }
    .article_column-text .h3-heading-pp, .article_column-text .h3-heading-ss {
        text-align: center;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 450px) {
    .article_column-image {
      height: 250px;
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="rebranding_container block-flex-wrap block-gap-50">
  <div class="rebranding-section-title block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center">
    <h2 class="h2-heading-ss">
      How to Identify a 
      <span class="h2-heading-pp">
        Fake Chanel Bag
      </span>
      : 6 Key Signs to Spot a Counterfeit
    </h2>
    <p class="body-text block-max-width">
      Chanel is one of the most iconic luxury fashion brands in the world, known for its timeless design, fine materials, and meticulous craftsmanship. This prestige makes <strong>Chanel bags a prime target for counterfeiters</strong>. If you're wondering <strong>how to tell if a Chanel bag is real</strong>, here are the most important signs to look out for.
<br><br>
Use this guide to avoid fakes and spot the differences between a <strong>real Chanel bag</strong> and a replica.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="article_columns-wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-start-center">
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "chanel-blog_seo-1.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Chanel Bag: Poor Leather Quality and Finish">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 1</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Poor Leather Quality and Finish</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
         <strong>Authentic Chanel bags</strong> are made from high-quality materials such as <strong>lambskin, caviar leather</strong>, or calfskin. These leathers feel soft, supple, and luxurious to the touch.
<br><br>
Fake Chanel bags often use:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Shiny, plastic-like leather</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Rough texture or uneven grain</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Unnatural chemical smells</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
        <span class="italic"><strong>Tip:</strong> Chanel caviar leather has a pebbled texture that’s consistent and deeply embossed — fakes often have shallow or inconsistent bumps.</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "chanel-blog_seo-2.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Chanel Bag: Incorrect or Inconsistent Serial Numbers">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 2</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Incorrect or Inconsistent Serial Numbers</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Every Chanel bag since the 1980s includes a <strong>serial number sticker</strong> and a matching authenticity card. These serials correspond to the year of production and follow a strict format.
<br><br>
Watch out for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Missing serial stickers</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Serial numbers that don’t match the year/model</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Sloppy font, wrong spacing, or misaligned numbers</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Authenticity card doesn’t match the serial</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "chanel-blog_seo-3.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Chanel Bag: Logo and CC Lock Misalignment">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 3</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Logo and CC Lock Misalignment</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          The <strong>Chanel CC logo</strong> is iconic — and also one of the most counterfeited features. On authentic bags:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">The right C overlaps the left C at the top</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">The left C overlaps the right C at the bottom</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">The lock is centered and straight, with precise spacing</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Fakes often get the proportions, spacing, or overlap direction wrong.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "chanel-blog_seo-4.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Chanel Bag: Lightweight or Tarnished Hardware">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 4</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Lightweight or Tarnished Hardware</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Chanel hardware is made from <strong>high-quality metal</strong>, often <strong>24K gold-plated</strong> in vintage models. It feels solid and heavy, with a polished, durable finish.
<br><br>
Counterfeit Chanel hardware may:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Feel hollow or flimsy</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Tarnish or fade quickly</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Have rough edges or incorrect engravings (like “CHANEL PARIS” font)</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "chanel-blog_seo-5.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Chanel Bag: Inconsistent Stitching and Quilting">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 5</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Inconsistent Stitching and Quilting</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Chanel bags feature <strong>precise stitching</strong> and iconic <strong>diamond quilting</strong>. The diamonds should line up perfectly across seams, flaps, and side panels.
<br><br>
Common stitching red flags:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Uneven or loose threads</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Misaligned quilting patterns</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "chanel-blog_seo-6.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="How to Identify a Fake Chanel Bag: Lining, Zipper, and Interior Tag Issues">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Step 6</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Lining, Zipper, and Interior Tag Issues</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Authentic Chanel bags are just as refined inside as they are outside. Look for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text"><strong>High-quality leather or fabric linings</strong></p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text"><strong>Smooth, sturdy zippers</strong> (often Lampo or YKK in vintage bags)</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">A clearly embossed interior tag with <strong>“Made in France” or “Made in Italy”</strong></p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Fakes often cut corners here, using:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
              <p class="body-text">Plastic zippers</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Loose or wrinkled lining</p>
            </li>
          <li>
              <p class="body-text">Poorly printed or off-centered tags</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

